::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:01.520 --> 00:00:03.650
Wealth, fame, power...

3
00:00:03.650 --> 00:00:07.820
Gold Roger, the King of the Pirates, obtained everything the world has to offer.

4
00:00:07.820 --> 00:00:11.660
What he said in his final moments drove countless souls to the seas.

5
00:00:11.660 --> 00:00:13.660
You want my treasure?

6
00:00:13.660 --> 00:00:15.450
Go ahead.

7
00:00:15.450 --> 00:00:16.660
Find it!

8
00:00:16.660 --> 00:00:19.250
Everything is right where I left it!

9
00:00:21.670 --> 00:00:26.380
People set their sights on the Grand Line in pursuit of their dreams.

10
00:00:26.380 --> 00:00:29.630
The world has truly entered the Great Pirate Era!

11
00:00:30.390 --> 00:00:35.640
Come aboard and bring along all your hopes and dreams

12
00:00:30.470 --> 00:00:35.640
Arittake no yume wo kaki atsume

13
00:00:35.850 --> 00:00:41.440
I know together we'll find everything we're looking for
Sagashi mono wo sagashi ni yuku no sa

14
00:00:41.770 --> 00:00:42.690
One Piece!
ONE PIECE

15
00:00:47.900 --> 00:00:52.700
Compasses? Not for me. Left them all behind
Rashinban nante juutai no moto

16
00:00:53.580 --> 00:00:58.500
I'm headed out to sea, with my heart serving as guide
Netsu ni ukasare kaji wo toru no sa

17
00:00:59.330 --> 00:01:04.540
Following the ancient map to the spot marked "X" reveals
Hokori kabutteta takara no chizu mo

18
00:01:04.540 --> 00:01:09.760
Yeah, it's only legendary till someone proves it's real
Tashikameta no nara densetsu janai!

19
00:01:11.380 --> 00:01:13.710
When the world's got you down,

20
00:01:11.380 --> 00:01:16.850
Kojin teki na arashi wa dare ka no

21
00:01:13.710 --> 00:01:16.850
lean on your crew, they'll turn it around

22
00:01:17.180 --> 00:01:22.190
Their biorhythm will carry you through
BIORHYTHM nokkatte

23
00:01:22.400 --> 00:01:24.230
We're gonna make the most of it
Omoi sugoseba ii!

24
00:01:26.110 --> 00:01:31.400
Come aboard and bring along all your hopes and dreams
Arittake no yume wo kaki atsume

25
00:01:31.610 --> 00:01:36.990
I know together we'll find everything we're looking for
Sagashi mono wo sagashi ni yuku no sa

26
00:01:37.330 --> 00:01:40.040
Got some change to my name,
POCKET no COIN

27
00:01:40.040 --> 00:01:43.250
and maybe you wanna be my friend?
Soreto YOU WANNA BE MY FRIEND?

28
00:01:43.540 --> 00:01:48.130
We are, we are on the cruise!
WE ARE, WE ARE ON THE CRUISE!

29
00:01:48.920 --> 00:01:49.760
WE ARE!

30
00:01:53.840 --> 00:01:57.760
The Fourth

31
00:02:04.560 --> 00:02:07.110
My hat! My straw hat!

32
00:02:07.110 --> 00:02:08.730
It's right there.

33
00:02:08.730 --> 00:02:10.400
Huh? Oh, yeah. Here it is.

34
00:02:10.400 --> 00:02:11.940
Rise and shine.

35
00:02:12.570 --> 00:02:14.320
Oh? Are those guys still...?

36
00:02:14.700 --> 00:02:15.870
They left...

37
00:02:15.870 --> 00:02:17.200
thanks to you.

38
00:02:17.200 --> 00:02:18.330
Me?

39
00:02:18.330 --> 00:02:22.000
Gin said, "I'll see you again
on the Grand Line."

40
00:02:23.750 --> 00:02:24.830
Gin said that...

41
00:02:25.330 --> 00:02:26.330
to you?

42
00:02:26.330 --> 00:02:27.840
He said it to you!

43
00:02:30.670 --> 00:02:33.590
Speaking of which,
since I drove them off,

44
00:02:33.590 --> 00:02:35.680
today is my last day
doing chores, right?

45
00:02:35.680 --> 00:02:36.800
Congrats.

46
00:02:37.140 --> 00:02:38.510
Which means that you'll...

47
00:02:38.510 --> 00:02:40.260
...not be going with you!

48
00:02:40.260 --> 00:02:41.930
I won't become a pirate.

49
00:02:42.430 --> 00:02:44.440
I'll keep working here as a cook

50
00:02:44.440 --> 00:02:47.610
until I get that old fart
to acknowledge my skills.

51
00:02:48.110 --> 00:02:50.070
I get it. I give up.

52
00:02:50.480 --> 00:02:52.570
Your hand hasn't given up yet!

53
00:02:56.490 --> 00:03:01.450
I can't leave here when every
last one of them is unreliable.

54
00:03:01.450 --> 00:03:04.540
But... I am hoping
to head out someday...

55
00:03:05.210 --> 00:03:06.830
to the Grand Line.

56
00:03:09.540 --> 00:03:11.300
Then let's go now.

57
00:03:11.300 --> 00:03:13.260
It's not the right time yet.

58
00:03:15.880 --> 00:03:17.220
Hey...

59
00:03:17.970 --> 00:03:19.970
have you heard of the All Blue?!

60
00:03:19.970 --> 00:03:21.100
Nope.

61
00:03:21.100 --> 00:03:23.350
You've seriously never heard of it?!

62
00:03:23.350 --> 00:03:24.850
That sea itself is a miracle!

63
00:03:26.940 --> 00:03:28.150
In that sea...

64
00:03:28.150 --> 00:03:31.360
The East Blue, West Blue,
North Blue, and South Blue...

65
00:03:31.360 --> 00:03:34.400
Fish from all four corners
of the world swim there!

66
00:03:36.860 --> 00:03:39.620
To us cooks, it's a dreamlike paradise!

67
00:03:39.990 --> 00:03:43.200
I mean, that's the Grand Line
for you. So, you've never...?

68
00:03:47.790 --> 00:03:50.670
He still lights up
when he talks about it...

69
00:03:52.040 --> 00:03:53.670
What a goofball.

70
00:03:59.300 --> 00:04:01.890
Time to eat, guys!

71
00:04:02.310 --> 00:04:03.850
Thank goodness...

72
00:04:02.350 --> 00:04:07.100
Employee Dining Room
2nd Floor, Baratie

73
00:04:03.850 --> 00:04:05.350
We can finally eat!

74
00:04:05.350 --> 00:04:07.100
Food! Food! Food!

75
00:04:13.020 --> 00:04:15.570
Hey, where are we supposed to sit?

76
00:04:15.570 --> 00:04:16.490
Where's our food?

77
00:04:16.490 --> 00:04:18.910
Seats are all taken.

78
00:04:19.570 --> 00:04:21.120
Sit on the floor and eat.

79
00:04:21.120 --> 00:04:22.620
No seats?

80
00:04:22.620 --> 00:04:24.120
How is that even possible?!

81
00:04:24.120 --> 00:04:26.410
This is a restaurant!

82
00:04:28.000 --> 00:04:29.250
Well, whatever...

83
00:04:29.250 --> 00:04:31.580
They're acting kinda weird...

84
00:04:33.590 --> 00:04:34.750
What's new?

85
00:04:36.590 --> 00:04:39.720
Hey! Who prepared
the soup this morning?!

86
00:04:40.300 --> 00:04:42.470
Hey, that was all me!
Pretty good, right?!

87
00:04:42.470 --> 00:04:44.720
I took extra care in making it today!

88
00:04:45.220 --> 00:04:47.310
I can't eat a vile soup like this!

89
00:04:47.310 --> 00:04:48.940
This is just slop!

90
00:04:56.190 --> 00:05:01.570
Hey... is human food not
to your liking, you damn tanuki?

91
00:05:02.450 --> 00:05:04.780
It's an art to make
something this bad.

92
00:05:04.780 --> 00:05:06.490
It makes me sick to my stomach!

93
00:05:08.290 --> 00:05:10.960
Sorry, but I'd stake my
reputation on this soup.

94
00:05:10.960 --> 00:05:13.750
You should go and get
your taste buds checked.

95
00:05:18.550 --> 00:05:20.510
Ugh! This is disgusting!

96
00:05:22.180 --> 00:05:24.100
I can't eat it!

97
00:05:25.720 --> 00:05:26.560
Right, guys?!

98
00:05:27.770 --> 00:05:29.180
It's inedible!

99
00:05:30.560 --> 00:05:32.520
This soup is revolting!

100
00:05:32.520 --> 00:05:34.060
I can't eat soup like this!

101
00:05:34.060 --> 00:05:36.520
This is terrible! Someone,
give me some water!

102
00:05:36.520 --> 00:05:38.900
Who are you bastards trying to fool?!

103
00:05:38.900 --> 00:05:42.150
You're a sham of a sous chef,
just so you know.

104
00:05:42.150 --> 00:05:43.780
You've gotten stale!

105
00:05:43.780 --> 00:05:47.160
We're tired of you solving
every problem with your feet.

106
00:05:47.160 --> 00:05:49.870
If the food's bad,
we'll tell you it's bad!

107
00:05:51.000 --> 00:05:51.750
Say what...?!

108
00:05:56.540 --> 00:05:57.630
– Chef Zeff!
– Chef Zeff!

109
00:05:57.630 --> 00:05:59.050
Old fart...!

110
00:06:01.010 --> 00:06:04.760
What is this vile scum of a soup?!

111
00:06:04.760 --> 00:06:06.510
If we serve something like this,

112
00:06:06.510 --> 00:06:08.680
we'll go out of business!

113
00:06:08.680 --> 00:06:10.980
Knock it off, you old fart!

114
00:06:10.980 --> 00:06:14.690
Just how is my soup different
from yours?! Tell me!

115
00:06:14.690 --> 00:06:16.770
You think this soup
compares to mine?!

116
00:06:19.650 --> 00:06:21.440
Don't flatter yourself!

117
00:06:23.860 --> 00:06:25.360
Chef Zeff punched him...

118
00:06:25.360 --> 00:06:26.990
Instead of kicking him?

119
00:06:26.990 --> 00:06:31.620
It's a billion years too early for you
to lecture me on cooking, little eggplant!

120
00:06:31.620 --> 00:06:35.710
I'm a man who has cooked
on seas across the world.

121
00:06:40.050 --> 00:06:41.130
Dammit!

122
00:06:51.640 --> 00:06:55.020
This soup is pretty tasty, you know...

123
00:06:55.020 --> 00:06:56.650
We know that.

124
00:06:56.650 --> 00:06:57.270
Huh?

125
00:06:57.270 --> 00:07:01.530
Everyone here knows
what a fantastic cook Sanji is.

126
00:07:02.360 --> 00:07:03.570
It's not bad at all.

127
00:07:03.570 --> 00:07:06.240
Yeah, this soup is exquisitely made.

128
00:07:06.240 --> 00:07:07.990
Boy, that was scary...

129
00:07:07.990 --> 00:07:09.740
He seriously snapped.

130
00:07:09.740 --> 00:07:10.990
He sure did.

131
00:07:16.920 --> 00:07:22.000
But that idiot won't listen
unless we go this far...

132
00:07:24.220 --> 00:07:25.680
Say, kid...

133
00:07:26.050 --> 00:07:29.680
You were saying that you wanted
a cook for your ship, right?

134
00:07:29.680 --> 00:07:33.350
I'm not asking you a favor or anything,

135
00:07:33.350 --> 00:07:36.310
but would you take that
little eggplant with you...

136
00:07:36.850 --> 00:07:38.730
to the Grand Line?

137
00:07:40.190 --> 00:07:42.230
The Grand Line...

138
00:07:42.230 --> 00:07:44.240
is his dream.

139
00:07:46.200 --> 00:07:49.780
Chef Zeff, you made us
put on a hell of a show.

140
00:07:49.780 --> 00:07:54.040
I thought for sure he'd figure it out
because of your bad acting.

141
00:07:55.160 --> 00:07:57.250
You were the bad actor here.

142
00:07:57.250 --> 00:07:58.750
I'll have another bowl!

143
00:07:58.750 --> 00:08:00.920
– Me, too!
– Me, too!

144
00:08:15.930 --> 00:08:19.650
I can hear everything,
you damn idiots...

145
00:08:21.440 --> 00:08:23.190
So what do you say, kid?

146
00:08:23.650 --> 00:08:24.610
No.

147
00:08:24.610 --> 00:08:25.480
– What?!
– What?!

148
00:08:26.690 --> 00:08:30.200
I thought you wanted
a cook for your ship.

149
00:08:31.280 --> 00:08:34.870
Or are you saying that
he's not good enough for you?

150
00:08:35.620 --> 00:08:39.870
It's not that he isn't good enough.
I really do want him to come with me.

151
00:08:40.500 --> 00:08:44.000
But he says that he wants to
keep working here as a cook.

152
00:08:44.000 --> 00:08:47.510
Even if you guys ask me
to take him, I can't.

153
00:08:48.130 --> 00:08:52.890
So you're saying that you can't agree
to it until he tells you so himself, huh?

154
00:08:53.220 --> 00:08:54.680
Exactly. More, please!

155
00:08:54.680 --> 00:08:57.310
Well... fair enough.

156
00:08:57.850 --> 00:08:59.690
But who knows if that screwed-up
brat can just say that he'll go...

157
00:08:59.690 --> 00:09:02.980
But who knows if that screwed-up
brat can just say that he'll go...

158
00:09:02.980 --> 00:09:06.940
I wouldn't hold your breath
for a stubborn idiot like that.

159
00:09:06.940 --> 00:09:08.150
More, please!

160
00:09:36.810 --> 00:09:37.600
Dammit...!

161
00:09:37.600 --> 00:09:38.430
Sanji!

162
00:09:38.430 --> 00:09:40.430
What is he? A fishman?

163
00:09:40.430 --> 00:09:43.190
He came from Fishman Island
to try our cuisine?

164
00:09:43.190 --> 00:09:45.400
Idiot! It's a human and a panda shark!

165
00:09:46.070 --> 00:09:46.940
What's going on?

166
00:09:46.940 --> 00:09:48.900
Oh! It's Yosaku!

167
00:09:49.320 --> 00:09:51.820
Ah... Big Bro Luffy!

168
00:09:51.820 --> 00:09:54.200
You're all by yourself?
Where's everyone else?

169
00:09:54.200 --> 00:09:55.280
Did you find Nami?

170
00:10:02.580 --> 00:10:04.960
We didn't actually catch up to her...

171
00:10:04.960 --> 00:10:09.460
but based on Big Sis Nami's heading,
we could guess her destination.

172
00:10:10.420 --> 00:10:12.510
We can bring her back, then.

173
00:10:13.090 --> 00:10:14.640
The thing is...

174
00:10:15.260 --> 00:10:21.180
if we're right about this, then she's
headed straight for trouble.

175
00:10:22.890 --> 00:10:25.770
In any case, we need
your help, Big Bro Luffy.

176
00:10:25.770 --> 00:10:26.980
Please come with me!

177
00:10:27.360 --> 00:10:31.070
Alright! I don't really get it,
but okay. Let's go!

178
00:10:39.620 --> 00:10:40.740
Wait!

179
00:10:41.750 --> 00:10:45.250
We both have foolish dreams.

180
00:10:48.670 --> 00:10:53.170
To achieve my goal—
to find the All Blue...

181
00:10:54.130 --> 00:10:55.090
Sanji?

182
00:10:56.260 --> 00:10:57.140
Yeah.

183
00:10:57.140 --> 00:11:00.600
I'll come along on your journey
to become King of the Pirates!

184
00:11:00.600 --> 00:11:01.430
Huh?

185
00:11:02.890 --> 00:11:06.020
I'll be the cook for your ship.

186
00:11:06.020 --> 00:11:07.980
Is that okay or not?

187
00:11:08.650 --> 00:11:09.940
It's okay!

188
00:11:09.940 --> 00:11:11.320
Alright!

189
00:11:11.320 --> 00:11:13.150
Congratulations, Big Bro Luffy!

190
00:11:13.150 --> 00:11:13.990
Yeah!

191
00:11:13.990 --> 00:11:15.400
– Yay! Yay!
– Yay! Yay!

192
00:11:15.400 --> 00:11:17.450
– We got a cook! We'll have good food!
– We got a cook! We'll have good food!

193
00:11:18.070 --> 00:11:19.950
That's what's happening, everyone.
Good food! Good food!

194
00:11:21.240 --> 00:11:23.870
Sorry for causing you
all sorts of trouble.

195
00:11:24.750 --> 00:11:25.870
You're pissin' me off...

196
00:11:25.870 --> 00:11:29.880
I wanted to kick you
out of here myself.

197
00:11:29.880 --> 00:11:33.090
And then you casually
decide just like that?

198
00:11:34.130 --> 00:11:38.090
Sorry for making you show off
your crappy acting skills.

199
00:11:38.090 --> 00:11:39.850
You knew?!

200
00:11:39.850 --> 00:11:41.310
I could hear you in there...

201
00:11:41.310 --> 00:11:42.560
You're all so stupid.

202
00:11:42.560 --> 00:11:43.770
We're what...?!

203
00:11:44.140 --> 00:11:47.730
So that means you're willing to go
that far to kick me out,

204
00:11:47.730 --> 00:11:49.100
huh, you old fart?!

205
00:11:49.690 --> 00:11:54.940
Why do you always talk like
such a disrespectful turd?!

206
00:11:56.450 --> 00:11:58.780
That's right, little eggplant!

207
00:11:59.450 --> 00:12:01.950
I couldn't care less for kids, anyway!

208
00:12:01.950 --> 00:12:07.210
Not a single day went by where I didn't
regret letting such a useless brat live.

209
00:12:07.960 --> 00:12:10.330
That makes this easier, you old fart!

210
00:12:10.330 --> 00:12:13.170
Savor the rest of
your life to the fullest!

211
00:12:14.420 --> 00:12:16.800
Is it okay for us to use
such a nice ship?

212
00:12:16.800 --> 00:12:19.010
Of course! It's Sanji's boat.

213
00:12:19.510 --> 00:12:21.850
You still need more?!

214
00:12:21.850 --> 00:12:23.510
Yeah. Give me more meat.

215
00:12:23.510 --> 00:12:26.390
Just how many days
will you be at sea?

216
00:12:26.390 --> 00:12:27.480
Don't know...

217
00:12:31.440 --> 00:12:33.570
Whoa!

218
00:12:33.570 --> 00:12:37.150
Old fart, is this the Sea Restaurant?

219
00:12:40.110 --> 00:12:42.070
Baratie Employee Guidelines
1. Serving customers equals love,
and love equals restaurant!
2. Motto! Motto!
It's my service motto!
3. A pleasant greeting equals service!
4. The customer is king!

220
00:12:57.880 --> 00:13:00.430
For example, Sanji...

221
00:13:01.180 --> 00:13:02.430
Yeah?

222
00:13:02.930 --> 00:13:07.390
Be they master criminals
or escaped convicts,

223
00:13:07.390 --> 00:13:13.860
if these damn bastards are starving
and find their way to this restaurant,

224
00:13:14.900 --> 00:13:18.360
that would give us reason
enough to keep fighting,

225
00:13:18.360 --> 00:13:20.610
wouldn't you say?

226
00:13:21.240 --> 00:13:22.320
Yeah!

227
00:13:23.370 --> 00:13:25.740
We're gonna be busy!

228
00:13:25.740 --> 00:13:28.620
We'll be fine 'cause I'm here!

229
00:13:38.420 --> 00:13:40.260
Ouch...

230
00:13:41.550 --> 00:13:42.680
Honestly...

231
00:13:44.970 --> 00:13:46.680
Thinner peels, little eggplant!

232
00:13:47.560 --> 00:13:49.680
That really hurt!

233
00:13:49.680 --> 00:13:54.100
When someone's focused on
their cooking, just shut up and watch!

234
00:13:54.100 --> 00:13:57.070
What?! Don't get smart
with me, you little eggplant!

235
00:13:57.070 --> 00:13:59.230
I'm not a little eggplant!

236
00:13:59.230 --> 00:14:02.570
You old fart!

237
00:14:04.030 --> 00:14:05.660
Try this.

238
00:14:05.660 --> 00:14:07.660
Did you make it by yourself?

239
00:14:08.240 --> 00:14:09.160
Yeah.

240
00:14:11.210 --> 00:14:12.040
How is it?

241
00:14:12.410 --> 00:14:13.580
Disgusting!

242
00:14:13.580 --> 00:14:15.540
This is inedible, you little eggplant!

243
00:14:16.250 --> 00:14:18.750
You old fart!

244
00:14:28.430 --> 00:14:30.850
Big Bro Cook sure is taking his time...

245
00:14:30.850 --> 00:14:31.680
Yeah...

246
00:14:41.860 --> 00:14:43.360
This is a long time coming!

247
00:14:43.360 --> 00:14:44.820
Get ready, Sanji!

248
00:14:51.790 --> 00:14:54.160
You guys will never kick his ass.

249
00:15:07.930 --> 00:15:09.260
Let's go.

250
00:15:09.260 --> 00:15:11.140
Shouldn't you say goodbye?

251
00:15:11.520 --> 00:15:12.770
It's fine.

252
00:15:12.770 --> 00:15:14.100
Sanji!

253
00:15:14.690 --> 00:15:17.350
Keep your feet dry.

254
00:15:32.490 --> 00:15:34.750
Chef Zeff!

255
00:15:36.250 --> 00:15:40.210
Thank you for every damn thing
you've done for me all these years!

256
00:15:40.750 --> 00:15:43.260
I'll never forget your kindness...

257
00:15:43.260 --> 00:15:44.760
for as long as I live!

258
00:16:04.190 --> 00:16:07.150
You asshole!

259
00:16:09.160 --> 00:16:12.160
I'll miss you, dammit!

260
00:16:12.160 --> 00:16:14.120
I'm gonna miss you!

261
00:16:28.010 --> 00:16:29.890
I'll miss you!

262
00:16:29.890 --> 00:16:32.140
You're making me cry, dammit!

263
00:16:39.310 --> 00:16:40.690
You're all idiots!

264
00:16:42.060 --> 00:16:45.530
Men should part without a word.

265
00:16:48.610 --> 00:16:51.700
Let's go! Set sail!

266
00:16:51.700 --> 00:16:55.450
I'll see you again, you damn bastards!

267
00:17:07.380 --> 00:17:13.050
If your conviction is such
that you no longer fear death...

268
00:17:13.510 --> 00:17:16.270
you'll surely find...

269
00:17:17.140 --> 00:17:19.060
the All Blue.

270
00:17:21.770 --> 00:17:25.110
Guys, customers are
gonna show up soon!

271
00:17:25.110 --> 00:17:27.780
Get to work already!

272
00:17:33.240 --> 00:17:40.100
As a kid, I had a dream of a dazzling treasure

273
00:17:40.300 --> 00:17:47.120
I had a map in my head that I knew would lead me

274
00:17:47.370 --> 00:17:54.220
Charted a course all on my own, so nobody would beat me

275
00:17:54.340 --> 00:18:01.480
The promised land was in my hand, drew a line in the sand

276
00:18:04.180 --> 00:18:06.860
Look where I am

277
00:18:09.090 --> 00:18:15.270
My one ambition's slipping right through my hands

278
00:18:15.610 --> 00:18:22.540
But if the world ever changes I'll call out your name

279
00:18:22.700 --> 00:18:29.620
We could return to a time when our lives were still the same

280
00:18:29.750 --> 00:18:36.750
Take me to the place where memories remain

281
00:18:36.850 --> 00:18:42.620
Please don't ever let them fade
